name: Moscow Davis and May Davis, husband and wife, Appellants, v. The Union Trust Company, a Corporation, Appellee

judges: Terrell, C. J., and Ellis and Brown, J. J., concur.
parties: Moscow Davis and May Davis, husband and wife, Appellants, v. The Union Trust Company, a Corporation, Appellee.

opinions.text:
Per Curiam.
This cause having heretofore been submitted to the Court upon the transcript of the record of the order herein, and briefs and argument of counsel for the respective parties and the record having béen seen and inspected, and the Court being now advised of its judgment to be given in the premises, it seems to the Court that there is no error in the said order. It is therefore, considered, ordered, and decreed by the Court that the said order of the Circuit Court be, and the same is hereby, affirmed.
Terrell, C. J., and Ellis and Brown, J. J., concur.
opinions.author: Per Curiam.

attorneys: J. McHenry Jones and Harvey E. Page, for Appellants;

Moscow Davis and May Davis, husband and wife, Appellants, v. The Union Trust Company, a Corporation, Appellee.
En Banc.

J. McHenry Jones and Harvey E. Page, for Appellants;
Jerry J. Sullivan, for Appellee.
